00:38.421 --> 00:41.130
Once upon a time,
there was a beautiful princess

00:41.213 --> 00:43.713
who lived in a big castle.

00:47.796 --> 00:50.046
Actually, the princess was a nice girl

00:50.130 --> 00:52.380
who lived in a huge house
that she had inherited,

00:52.463 --> 00:55.213
and half of her salary went
to maintaining it.

00:57.505 --> 01:00.046
The princess was full of optimism,

01:00.130 --> 01:04.754
dreams, hopes, and tons of carbohydrates.

01:06.421 --> 01:08.921
But now, all that's left are the carbs.

01:09.921 --> 01:13.880
How does a nice, good-hearted princess,

01:13.963 --> 01:17.088
who is capable of eating
a family-size pizza by herself,

01:17.255 --> 01:18.546
end up like this?

01:18.838 --> 01:21.213
Just like everything
that's wrong with the world,

01:21.296 --> 01:22.796
it's the fault of...

01:24.213 --> 01:25.213
a man.

01:25.755 --> 01:28.505
THE DAY BEFORE

01:28.796 --> 01:29.671
No!

01:38.755 --> 01:41.421
- Hi, lovebug!
- Hi, Fe.

01:42.255 --> 01:45.588
Finally, my love!

01:46.213 --> 01:49.630
I wasn't able to talk much these days,
but I promise I'll make it up to you!

01:49.713 --> 01:51.796
Listen,
I want to talk to you about something.

01:51.880 --> 01:54.588
I know that last time we were talking

01:54.671 --> 01:58.005
about how the distance sucks.
It really sucks.

01:58.088 --> 01:59.421
We both get weird.

01:59.505 --> 02:01.880
Yes, yes.
I want to talk to you about that.

02:01.963 --> 02:06.255
And it's clearly making us feel weird.
Of course we're going to feel weird.

02:06.338 --> 02:10.005
Though I have to say
the phone sex hasn't been bad.

02:10.088 --> 02:12.588
Though I get nervous
about the United States listening

02:12.671 --> 02:15.130
to our calls because...
that's embarrassing!

02:15.213 --> 02:17.880
- Fe.
- What? What do you want to say?

02:18.921 --> 02:21.963
I've been thinking. I don't know...

02:24.755 --> 02:28.046
I'm sorry to say this here, okay? But...

02:30.046 --> 02:31.880
I think that we need...

02:32.880 --> 02:34.213
a break, okay?

02:36.588 --> 02:37.505
A break?

02:39.546 --> 02:42.046
- When? How?
- A break.

02:43.380 --> 02:44.296
Look...

02:46.380 --> 02:50.963
I think that we need more space.

02:52.130 --> 02:53.921
More space?

02:56.046 --> 02:58.546
Ten-thousand kilometers
isn't enough for you?

02:58.630 --> 02:59.630
Fe...

03:00.255 --> 03:01.546
you know what I mean.

03:02.046 --> 03:02.963
No.

03:08.671 --> 03:09.671
Damn...

03:11.130 --> 03:12.463
I'm really sorry.

03:13.463 --> 03:16.630
I didn't want it to be like this.

03:17.255 --> 03:18.796
I don't get it. Are you break...

03:19.963 --> 03:21.880
Are you breaking up with me?

03:28.630 --> 03:31.505
I think it's for the best.
Seeing as I'm not...

03:31.588 --> 03:33.171
- Yes? What?
- I think...

03:33.255 --> 03:35.296
- I think we need...
- No. Hello?

03:35.380 --> 03:37.713
- ...space.
- Hello? Hi?

03:37.796 --> 03:39.421
- It's not me...
- Hello?

03:39.505 --> 03:41.963
Matías? Hello, Matías?

03:42.046 --> 03:43.880
Hello?

03:54.755 --> 03:57.380
They say that grief has five stages.

03:57.463 --> 04:00.963
I went through all of them in one night.
And over WhatsApp.

04:03.255 --> 04:06.213
Hey, lovebug, honey.
How are you? Listen...

04:06.296 --> 04:08.463
I understand what you're going through,
okay?

04:08.546 --> 04:09.755
It will pass.

04:09.838 --> 04:10.963
DENIAL

04:11.046 --> 04:13.505
Besides, Mercury's in retrograde,
the Moon's waxing,

04:13.588 --> 04:15.421
and we're all basically water!

04:15.505 --> 04:19.796
So take it easy, rest up, and call me
when you're better so we can talk.

04:19.880 --> 04:22.005
Kisses. I love you. Take it easy.

04:22.338 --> 04:25.671
Are you seriously not going to reply?
Really?

04:25.755 --> 04:26.921
ANGER

04:27.005 --> 04:31.296
Do you think this is what I deserve
after six years in this relationship?

04:31.380 --> 04:34.546
Huh? No!
Well, I have news for you, Matías.

04:34.630 --> 04:36.963
You're not the ideal size. Okay?

04:37.046 --> 04:41.421
You're far from it!
The ideal size is big! You idiot!

04:41.505 --> 04:45.546
You screwed up! I'm never going to Madrid,
and it's all your fault!

04:45.755 --> 04:49.838
Who the hell buys a board game
in Portuguese?

04:50.130 --> 04:52.088
Fucking hipster!

04:55.880 --> 05:00.213
You'll never play me like this again!

05:00.838 --> 05:03.130
Listen, Matías, I've been thinking.

05:04.505 --> 05:08.671
This can't happen again, okay?
We can't disrespect each other like this.

05:08.755 --> 05:11.005
It's a line we can't cross, okay?

05:11.088 --> 05:12.630
BARGAINING

05:12.713 --> 05:16.713
Now, I understand there are things
that you don't like about me.

05:17.338 --> 05:19.838
I don't know what they are.
You never told me.

05:20.505 --> 05:24.088
There are things I don't like about you,
but I'm not throwing them in your face.

05:24.171 --> 05:27.338
And if you want me to change, well,
we'll talk about it.

05:27.421 --> 05:28.921
Everything in life is change.

05:29.005 --> 05:32.796
Then there's resistance to change,
and then change again.

05:32.880 --> 05:34.755
So if you want me to change, I will.

05:35.505 --> 05:40.713
I'm willing to eat pineapple pizza,
Matías.

05:40.796 --> 05:43.130
WON'T YOU REPLY?
I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS

05:43.213 --> 05:44.880
Pineapple pizza.

05:46.671 --> 05:50.671
DEPRESSION

05:55.130 --> 05:58.755
I SEE THAT YOU'RE ONLINE

06:03.838 --> 06:07.838
ACCEPTANCE

06:14.630 --> 06:17.546
NETFLIX PRESENTS

06:24.380 --> 06:27.421
If there is something positive
about waking up

06:27.505 --> 06:32.796
in an empty bathtub, hungover,
and with pizza in your hair...

06:33.088 --> 06:36.380
it's the deceptive feeling that,
from here on,

06:36.463 --> 06:38.671
things can only get better.

06:38.880 --> 06:43.963
María Fe Palacios,
you will not be that kind of girl.

06:53.005 --> 06:54.296
She's not opening the door?

06:55.046 --> 06:57.880
No, she already opened it.
It's just that I love standing here,

06:57.963 --> 07:01.338
waiting to grow gills
with this lovely humidity, Santiago.

07:02.963 --> 07:05.380
I love the humidity. Mexico is too dry.

07:05.463 --> 07:07.005
Lima's climate is perfect.

07:07.088 --> 07:09.963
You say that because you've only
lived here for 45 minutes.

07:10.088 --> 07:12.046
No, I've been here for three years.

07:12.130 --> 07:14.088
And you still can't get rid
of your accent?

07:15.421 --> 07:17.713
We haven't seen each other
since that time, right?

07:17.796 --> 07:19.755
It's been ages! Go figure.

07:20.338 --> 07:23.213
- Since Fe's party?
- Since your ex-boss's going-away party.

07:23.713 --> 07:25.755
You have such a good memory.

07:31.088 --> 07:32.088
Fe!

07:34.588 --> 07:37.755
So, are you here to have breakfast
with my friend?

07:38.005 --> 07:38.838
Or what?

07:42.046 --> 07:44.380
Yes, you, with a penis...

07:44.463 --> 07:51.046
Tell me, what do you have in there,
where your heart is supposed to be?

07:51.380 --> 07:53.171
I guess you received one of these, too.

07:53.255 --> 07:56.421
Seven, and the last two were
of her singing Alejandro Sanz.

07:56.671 --> 07:58.671
Alejandro Sanz from the 2000s
or the 1990s?

07:58.755 --> 07:59.880
From the '90s.

08:00.963 --> 08:02.338
Hey.

08:02.588 --> 08:04.546
Hey, friends!

08:04.630 --> 08:06.713
What are you doing here? How are you?

08:06.796 --> 08:08.421
We've been calling you all day.

08:08.505 --> 08:10.296
I didn't hear because of my headphones.

08:10.380 --> 08:11.755
- Can I borrow this?
- Sure.

08:11.838 --> 08:13.421
Did you come to take me to work?

08:13.505 --> 08:16.255
We were worried,
because of what happened last night.

08:18.338 --> 08:22.046
Matías and I broke up, but don't worry.
Everything's fine.

08:22.130 --> 08:26.088
But thanks for coming, my friend.
You're the best. I love you.

08:26.171 --> 08:29.046
But I'm not gonna get dramatic
like a 16-year-old girl, right?

08:29.130 --> 08:30.463
Life goes on.

08:30.546 --> 08:33.296
- It's a new day. Let's go and get to work.
- Hold on.

08:33.380 --> 08:36.380
Are you sure you don't need
to stay in bed, cry a bit,

08:36.462 --> 08:37.546
or eat some ice cream?

08:37.630 --> 08:38.712
Or fuck somebody?

08:38.796 --> 08:41.880
No, I really don't need any of that.
What I need is to get to work.

08:41.962 --> 08:43.087
Let's go. Think fast.

08:44.130 --> 08:46.463
I got it. Okay, go with him. It's fine.

08:46.546 --> 08:48.380
- All right, that's the spirit.
- Right!

08:48.463 --> 08:50.213
I'll call you later so we can talk.

08:50.296 --> 08:52.671
- I could sleep over.
- I'm fine, my friend.

08:52.880 --> 08:55.755
- Okay, don't drive fast.
- Bye, beautiful.

08:58.796 --> 08:59.838
Sure you're okay?

09:00.213 --> 09:01.963
- Stop it, I'm fine!
- Okay.

09:03.880 --> 09:06.338
I'm sure he likes you,
he's always smiling...

09:06.421 --> 09:08.671
Santiago, here's your decaf latte.

09:08.963 --> 09:10.880
You're the best person in this office.

09:10.963 --> 09:13.255
- After you!
- My friend!

09:15.755 --> 09:17.588
Don't kid yourself, it's not gonna happen.

09:17.671 --> 09:19.130
You never know.

09:19.338 --> 09:21.588
- Let's go.
- We're flanning. Flanning.

09:21.671 --> 09:23.380
Let's get flanning.

09:24.546 --> 09:25.838
Flan-tastic.

09:25.921 --> 09:27.546
- Flan-atic.
- Flan-atic.

09:28.546 --> 09:30.796
Let's start creating. The word flan.

09:31.213 --> 09:32.963
Look at what I have, Ramiro.

09:33.046 --> 09:35.796
If we want intrigue,
we could launch something like...

09:35.880 --> 09:38.005
- Flan, flan, flan, flan...
- I like that.

09:38.088 --> 09:39.838
- Flan, flan, flan!
- More of the same.

09:39.921 --> 09:42.671
Wouldn't you like some delicious
flan-ch toast for breakfast?

09:42.755 --> 09:43.671
Good!

09:43.755 --> 09:46.838
Give us this day... our daily flan.

09:46.921 --> 09:48.796
- Fluorescent.
- Yes, fluorescent.

09:48.880 --> 09:53.296
- Fluorescent doesn't have "flan" in it.
- The young lady's killed our creativity.

09:53.380 --> 09:55.838
- What? Fine, I won't say anything.
- Let's wrap this up.

09:56.046 --> 09:57.713
Charly has something to say.

09:57.796 --> 09:59.671
I was saying that, once again,

09:59.755 --> 10:02.046
- we have exceeded expectations.
- Exceeded!

10:02.130 --> 10:05.671
The cocktail potato campaign
has reached 50,000 views.

10:05.755 --> 10:09.630
And not just that,
the hashtag that we created is trending.

10:09.713 --> 10:10.588
Trending topic!

10:10.671 --> 10:12.380
- Gastón himself shared it.
- Gastón!

10:12.463 --> 10:15.171
Very good! Congratulations, genius!

10:15.713 --> 10:16.546
Thanks, Rami.

10:16.630 --> 10:17.671
A round of applause.

10:17.755 --> 10:20.046
- Applaud.
- Give him a hand.

10:20.338 --> 10:21.755
We're working on something for Cannes.

10:21.838 --> 10:24.671
Diego, make sure
that account planning inflates the results

10:24.755 --> 10:26.505
to show more sales potential.
Mafe, what are you up to?

10:26.755 --> 10:30.296
I've just finished the campaign
for the cream, Smoothness.

10:30.796 --> 10:33.921
You did what I said, right?
You used women's empowerment and all that?

10:34.005 --> 10:36.088
Yes, "smoother skin, stronger women."

10:36.171 --> 10:39.713
Add some color to it, add some flowers,
make it look more feminine.

10:39.796 --> 10:41.130
He can help you.

10:43.046 --> 10:46.630
Nobody makes fun of them here.
It's not contagious.

10:47.713 --> 10:48.796
Just joking, okay?

10:49.838 --> 10:52.505
- You're doing the pads?
- Yes. I finished the campaign.

10:52.588 --> 10:54.505
A small one for Facebook,
but it's ready.

10:54.588 --> 10:57.671
- So you can take the cooking oil campaign.
- The cooking oil!

10:57.963 --> 11:01.171
It's a good one. It has flavor,
it's got personality. You'll like it.

11:01.255 --> 11:04.338
It's also street-smart.
Great. Let's do this, babe.

11:04.421 --> 11:05.838
Let's make it tasty.

11:07.630 --> 11:09.546
Give it some spice.

11:09.671 --> 11:11.588
Now, I have to choose...

11:12.921 --> 11:16.963
which of you will be in charge
of our new client's campaign.

11:17.046 --> 11:19.671
The annual and regional campaign.

11:20.463 --> 11:21.588
Who's up for it?

11:22.130 --> 11:24.338
Rami,
Charly and I are very busy right now.

11:24.421 --> 11:25.796
No, we're not very busy.

11:25.880 --> 11:28.046
In advertising, you can't be too busy.

11:28.130 --> 11:30.546
There's no such thing.
I'm going to tell you a story.

11:31.338 --> 11:33.546
The year was 1994,
and I thought I was too busy.

11:34.088 --> 11:37.380
I was assigned
Coca-Cola's regional campaign.

11:37.463 --> 11:38.713
Coca-Cola, okay?

11:39.630 --> 11:42.921
I created it while I was in the shower.
Boom! It was a hit.

11:43.005 --> 11:46.046
Five Golden Lion Awards.
I thought I was too busy.

11:46.130 --> 11:48.713
Excuse me, Ramiro,
but I'd like to do that campaign.

11:48.796 --> 11:50.546
You're too busy with the cooking oil.

11:51.588 --> 11:52.713
- Who can do it?
- I can.

11:53.880 --> 11:57.171
- But you're...
- No, I'm done. I just finished it.

11:58.463 --> 11:59.630
That's enough!

12:00.255 --> 12:02.796
- Mafe will do it.
- Great. What's the product?

12:03.380 --> 12:04.505
Tissues.

12:04.921 --> 12:07.380
It's what women like. Time to cry, honey.

12:07.880 --> 12:08.713
Sound good?

12:08.796 --> 12:11.880
There is one thing
you can always count on,

12:11.963 --> 12:16.005
and that is the universe's
twisted sense of humor.

12:45.755 --> 12:46.588
Fe...

12:47.255 --> 12:50.130
I left six months ago,
and you still haven't fixed that door?

12:51.921 --> 12:54.088
Are you waiting for me
to come back and fix it?

12:56.963 --> 12:57.921
I like it like this.

12:58.796 --> 13:03.213
Yeah, it gives it an air of...
I saw it on Pinterest.

13:05.380 --> 13:11.171
This isn't happening. He's not here.
He's in my head.

13:11.963 --> 13:14.213
In my head...

13:14.296 --> 13:15.171
It's in my head.

13:27.255 --> 13:29.796
Are you watching Game of Thrones
without me?

13:29.963 --> 13:31.755
- That's sacrilege.
- Listen...

13:32.421 --> 13:34.630
You've got some nerve.
You broke up with me.

13:34.713 --> 13:36.463
I can watch any series I feel like.

13:36.546 --> 13:40.546
Yeah, but this is like pure hate.
Are you declaring war against me?

13:40.630 --> 13:42.421
Sorry, there's nothing you can do.

13:44.130 --> 13:46.630
I can show up
every time there's a sex scene.

13:46.713 --> 13:48.546
So I can remind you of when we...

14:00.630 --> 14:03.130
This is the best bed in the world.

14:03.546 --> 14:05.546
Holy shit...

14:06.046 --> 14:08.380
Remember the first night
we slept in this house?

14:08.630 --> 14:11.630
There was only this mattress.
There wasn't anything else here.

14:12.130 --> 14:13.671
Not even a table for us to eat on.

14:14.213 --> 14:17.213
But I opened a bottle of wine...

14:17.755 --> 14:19.546
and we just talked for three hours.

14:22.796 --> 14:26.421
And then I couldn't stop laughing
because we spilled the wine.

14:27.755 --> 14:29.880
We spent hours cleaning that up.

14:30.838 --> 14:32.463
We threw salt on the rug, right?

14:34.005 --> 14:36.546
I always remember that, too.

14:49.755 --> 14:52.296
You've been getting me
out of bed for two weeks at 11 p.m.,

14:52.380 --> 14:54.005
and you make me come over.

14:54.463 --> 14:57.130
I can't do this anymore. I'm serious.

14:58.088 --> 14:59.296
I'm sorry.

15:00.421 --> 15:02.880
Look, I know you're going
through a rough patch.

15:02.963 --> 15:04.630
It's shitty, I know.

15:05.588 --> 15:07.213
But, know what I think?

15:07.463 --> 15:10.338
You shouldn't live here by yourself.
This house is too big.

15:10.421 --> 15:11.796
That's why you're like this.

15:13.130 --> 15:14.713
Why don't we look for a roommate?

15:15.255 --> 15:16.963
- Move in with me.
- No.

15:17.046 --> 15:18.796
- Please.
- No way.

15:18.880 --> 15:22.546
We'd kill each other.
We wouldn't last one week.

15:22.755 --> 15:25.380
Besides, I've just renewed my lease.
I can't.

15:25.755 --> 15:26.755
Fine.

15:28.463 --> 15:30.630
I can help you find a roommate
if you'd like.

15:30.713 --> 15:32.505
We can set up interviews. How about it?

15:34.130 --> 15:37.546
No, I'm fine like this, really.

15:37.630 --> 15:38.880
I'll get over it.

15:52.463 --> 15:54.463
Okay, help me find a roommate.

15:55.380 --> 15:56.505
Yes, tomorrow.

15:56.588 --> 15:58.130
- Are you serious?
- Yes, please.

15:58.338 --> 16:00.088
Hi, Romina, how are you? I'm Natalia.

16:00.171 --> 16:01.671
- Hi!
- Nice to meet you.

16:01.755 --> 16:03.088
- Honey, no...
- What?

16:03.171 --> 16:04.838
You have something on your face.

16:06.046 --> 16:07.588
Are you two...

16:08.755 --> 16:09.630
a couple?

16:09.713 --> 16:11.546
- No!
- No.

16:12.255 --> 16:13.963
20,0000! #ILoveEveryone.

16:14.046 --> 16:15.505
# BlessedAllTheWay.

16:15.588 --> 16:18.463
Because we owe it to our audience.
Right? It's super crazy.

16:18.546 --> 16:20.796
They pay you to post photos on Instagram?

16:20.880 --> 16:22.713
Of course!
And they give me free clothes.

16:22.796 --> 16:25.630
Like these.
Don't you love them? I can give you some.

16:25.713 --> 16:28.671
Oh, I'm sorry.
I don't think they'll fit you.

16:28.755 --> 16:30.921
There's, like, a leak here, right?

16:31.005 --> 16:34.296
- What?
- Look at my hands. My hands got wet.

16:34.380 --> 16:37.213
- There's no pipe here...
- Oh, isn't this dishcloth a bit sticky?

16:37.296 --> 16:39.213
- Maybe...
- I'll wash it.

16:39.296 --> 16:41.588
So which of you would move in here?

16:41.796 --> 16:43.005
- Both of us.
- Both of us.

16:43.088 --> 16:45.088
Oh, honey, we said it at the same time.

16:45.171 --> 16:47.255
I'm sure a brand
could get confused one day

16:47.338 --> 16:50.046
and send me an XL or large.
I'd be happy to give it to you.

16:50.130 --> 16:52.338
You have to wash this now, or else...

16:53.171 --> 16:55.463
Watch out!

16:55.630 --> 16:57.088
Didn't you see that fly?

16:57.296 --> 16:59.671
- Is he your husband?
- No.

17:00.963 --> 17:03.880
What's this? How crazy!

17:04.171 --> 17:05.213
You're so funny.

17:05.546 --> 17:08.046
- Wait.
- Hey.

17:09.463 --> 17:12.671
There was something dead there.
Now there are living things. Name them.

17:12.963 --> 17:15.880
We'll have to use your room
so we're more comfortable.

17:15.963 --> 17:18.755
- Isn't that right, my love?
- Yes. Whatever she says.

17:19.880 --> 17:21.838
So you lived together,
but weren't married.

17:21.921 --> 17:23.546
Yeah, that's normal, right?

17:23.921 --> 17:26.755
Yes, don't worry. I'm not judging you.

17:27.213 --> 17:28.421
But God is.

17:29.046 --> 17:31.755
What is this? It's cute.

17:31.838 --> 17:36.380
The parties here have to end before 8 p.m.
I have to go to bed on time.

17:36.463 --> 17:38.046
We don't throw a lot of parties.

17:38.130 --> 17:40.505
- Hey. She stole my magnet.
- What?

17:40.588 --> 17:42.088
- She stole the magnet!
- I swear.

17:42.171 --> 17:44.005
- Tell her to give it back.
- You tell her!

17:44.296 --> 17:46.296
Okay. Well...

17:46.755 --> 17:49.671
It's fixed. You won't have any more issues
with your pipes.

17:49.755 --> 17:53.838
Thank you, Santi. That's great.
I love you. Thanks, you're the best.

17:55.046 --> 17:57.963
Why the long faces?
Was it really that bad?

17:58.671 --> 18:00.463
Yeah, looks like I'm gonna live alone.

18:00.546 --> 18:03.755
