18:47.630 --> 18:48.921
That's powerful.

18:49.171 --> 18:51.796
- I'm Natalia, María Fe's best friend.
- Sorry. How are you?

18:53.213 --> 18:54.421
How are you, beautiful?

18:54.505 --> 18:56.505
- Good. And you are?
- Caro, Carolina.

18:56.588 --> 18:58.171
Caro or Carolina, either is fine.

18:58.421 --> 18:59.463
I'm a vegetarian.

18:59.546 --> 19:02.338
Sometimes I eat chicken,
but I'm a vegetarian.

19:02.505 --> 19:05.421
I do yoga every day at 7 a.m.
I wake up super early.

19:05.505 --> 19:07.463
Except Wednesdays.
They're yellow, so I can't.

19:07.546 --> 19:08.380
Of course.

19:08.463 --> 19:10.088
I don't believe
in long-term relationships.

19:10.171 --> 19:12.005
But I do believe Paul McCartney is dead

19:12.088 --> 19:15.963
and the man who passes for him
is a double. Just like Avril Lavigne.

19:18.255 --> 19:19.713
- I'm going.
- It's a...

19:19.796 --> 19:21.713
We're having a problem with the pipes,
but he'll fix it.

19:21.796 --> 19:24.463
Everything happens for a reason,
no worries.

19:24.546 --> 19:25.546
How beautiful.

19:25.630 --> 19:27.255
Oh, I'm sorry.

19:27.463 --> 19:31.213
I brought you all something to try.

19:31.296 --> 19:32.921
Thank you.

19:33.005 --> 19:35.130
- They're the best brownies in town.
- Thank you.

19:35.213 --> 19:37.088
- Did you make them?
- Yes, I made them.

19:39.005 --> 19:41.796
Don't worry, there's no pot in them.
I have pot for later if you'd like,

19:41.880 --> 19:43.588
- but that doesn't have any.
- Okay.

19:45.588 --> 19:47.755
I'm having a mouthgasm.

19:47.838 --> 19:50.671
These are definitely
the best brownies I've ever tried.

19:50.755 --> 19:53.463
That's another thing about me,
I always tell the truth.

19:54.505 --> 19:56.338
- And...
- And...

19:56.421 --> 19:59.380
Caro, when could you move in?

19:59.463 --> 20:00.296
Carolina...

20:01.338 --> 20:03.505
Everything's fine.

20:03.588 --> 20:06.755
I'm fine with moving in now.
I think you guys need help, right?

20:14.338 --> 20:16.880
You're so good at that.
Plants always die on me.

20:16.963 --> 20:19.171
- But you paint furniture beautifully.
- Thanks.

20:19.255 --> 20:22.171
This whole gardening thing
gets me very nervous.

20:22.255 --> 20:24.505
- But do you paint?
- No.

20:24.588 --> 20:26.505
I've never followed
Dr. Miyagi's practices.

20:27.546 --> 20:30.963
Mr. Miyagi.
Miyagi was a mister, not a doctor.

20:31.046 --> 20:32.921
- It's Mr. Miyagi.
- I'm sorry.

20:33.005 --> 20:33.963
Could you help us

20:34.046 --> 20:36.171
- and paint the walls?
- No.

20:36.255 --> 20:38.005
You could ask your boyfriend to help.

20:38.088 --> 20:40.255
You can relax a bit
and get off the computer.

20:40.338 --> 20:44.630
Hey, how many of these have you smoked?
Who said I have a boyfriend?

20:44.713 --> 20:48.588
Isn't the Mexican your boyfriend?
The one who curses with a Mexican accent.

20:48.671 --> 20:50.380
There's no way I'd be with him, carnal.

20:50.463 --> 20:51.921
He's a cute guy, isn't he?

20:52.005 --> 20:54.588
I mean, he's got good energy
and all that.

20:54.671 --> 20:56.963
Yeah, but don't insist.
She doesn't like those things.

20:57.046 --> 20:57.963
She's like that.

20:58.130 --> 21:01.296
He's a player.
Anyway, I think he's kind of dumb.

21:01.796 --> 21:06.171
- You liked him the first time you saw him.
- Caro, are you seeing anyone?

21:06.338 --> 21:09.963
Yeah, two or three people,
depending on the situation.

21:10.130 --> 21:13.171
I like connecting
with as many people as possible.

21:13.796 --> 21:16.463
And you? How long have you been
with your boyfriend for?

21:16.671 --> 21:20.380
No, we're not together anymore.
We lasted six years.

21:20.463 --> 21:22.880
- Oh, six years?
- Yes.

21:22.963 --> 21:26.171
That's how long a squirrel lives.
What happened?

21:26.338 --> 21:29.755
He's an architect.
He helped me fix the house up.

21:29.838 --> 21:32.838
And he went to Spain
to get his master's degree.

21:33.005 --> 21:34.796
And distance always gets in the way.

21:34.880 --> 21:38.963
But I think it's a phase,
and he'll get over it.

21:42.463 --> 21:43.505
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

21:43.588 --> 21:46.546
Let's take a selfie
so people can see we're doing things.

21:46.630 --> 21:48.380
- Great!
- Yeah.

21:49.671 --> 21:51.338
Okay. We're all happy, right?

21:55.880 --> 21:56.713
Okay.

21:56.921 --> 21:58.630
- Great, thanks.
- We're done.

21:59.296 --> 22:01.505
Be careful, this leaves a horrible stain.

22:01.880 --> 22:03.880
- I'm going to tag you, okay?
- Okay.

22:12.130 --> 22:13.755
TOUGH SEMESTER,
BUT WORTH THE REWARD

22:23.421 --> 22:25.588
DANIELA GARCIA
ARCHITECT AND ANIMAL LOVER

22:31.630 --> 22:36.046
THE BEST PART OF THE SCHOOL YEAR

22:47.255 --> 22:48.338
